And I'm incredibly
competitive.

00:13:16.400 --> 00:13:19.190
I mean, I race my kids up
staircases and I win.

00:13:19.190 --> 00:13:21.046
I'm like, doon!

00:13:21.046 --> 00:13:21.860
And they're like, Dad!

00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:22.320
And I'm like, what?

00:13:22.320 --> 00:13:23.190
Dude, suck a--

00:13:23.190 --> 00:13:24.170
you know.

00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:26.160
And I do it because I
won't always win.

00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:27.510
One day-- they're 12 and 10.

00:13:27.510 --> 00:13:29.810
And within five years, they're
going to beat me.

00:13:29.810 --> 00:13:31.510
My wife's like, you've
got to give up.

00:13:31.510 --> 00:13:32.420
I said, I'm not going
to give up.

00:13:32.420 --> 00:13:33.360
They're going to need
to beat me.

00:13:33.360 --> 00:13:34.350
So anyway.

00:13:34.350 --> 00:13:35.090
Scrabble--

00:13:35.090 --> 00:13:37.830
and sometimes I let them win,
because you don't want to be

00:13:37.830 --> 00:13:40.410
so, so mean.

00:13:40.410 --> 00:13:42.370
Although, I'd rather not.

00:13:42.370 --> 00:13:45.510
But my agent said look, you're
not going to win.

00:13:45.510 --> 00:13:47.350
I'm like, thanks, Sandy.

00:13:47.350 --> 00:13:48.560
And he'd be like, no, no, no.

00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:49.400
You're a good chef.

00:13:49.400 --> 00:13:52.710
It's that the winner's replacing
Mario Batali, a New

00:13:52.710 --> 00:13:54.610
York Italian chef.

